des:
Your wish is our command. With Geeni skill, you can now interact with your Geeni smart home devices by voice. 

You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off, dim your lights, or turn smart plugs on or off. You can also group multiple devices together into a "Living Room" group and say “Alexa, turn on living room”.

To tell Alexa which device to control, use the names you set up already in the Geeni app, or create an Alexa group, like "Bedroom" or "Downstairs", and add the device to the group.
Once you know the name or group of your devices, you can say commands like these: 
“Alexa, turn on the bedroom light.”
“Alexa, turn off the bedroom light.”
“Alexa, set the bedroom light to 50%.”
“Alexa, brighten the bedroom light.”
“Alexa, dim the bedroom light to 25%.”
“Alexa, set bedroom light to red.”

Here’s a step by step guide:
(1) Download our "Geeni" app in Google Play or the iOS App Store;
(2) Register a new account in the "Geeni" app (or log in if you’re already registered);
(3) Connect the Geeni smart devices and use the “Geeni” app to configure them;
(4) IMPORTANT: You can rename your devices in the Geeni app, and Alexa will refer to them by the same name. So if you rename a smart bulb to “Living Room” or give it a nickname like “Blossom”, then Alexa will use that same name or nickname later on;
(5) If your Echo device is not configured yet, download the Amazon "Alexa" app from the Amazon Appstore, Google Play or the iOS App Store and follow the instructions given by the app;
(6) Search the Alexa Skills directory for "Geeni" and select it, the skill’s detail card will open;
(7) Click “Enable skill” and you'll be navigated to a login page, follow the instructions on the page to complete linking;
(8) Tell Echo "Alexa, discover my devices". Wait for Echo to say "Search complete";
(9) Now the setup is finished. You can interact with the skill using the commands described above. 

Currently, this skill supports the Geeni smart plugs and smart bulbs. If you have any problems, please contact us at support@mygeeni.com
